EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to elections; revising certain deadlines relating to
the return of mail ballots; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, if a mail ballot is returned by mail, the mail ballot must be:
2 (1) postmarked on or before the day of the election; and (2) received by the county
3 or city clerk by 5 p.m. on the fourth day following the election. (NRS 293.269921,
4 293.269923, 293C.26321, 293C.26323) This bill instead requires mail ballots that
5 are returned by mail to be postmarked on or before the last day of the period for
6 early voting and received by the county or city clerk before the time set for the
7 closing of the polls on the day of the election.
